{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/episode-43-the-asian-bermedia-triangle/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Episode 43. The Asian BerMEDIA Triangle","tags":["recommendations","media"],"date":"2020-11-30T13:00:00.000Z","category":"episode","imgsrc":"assets/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.jpg","link":"<iframe src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed-podcast/episode/3AzPQwMgguTbxmxVwPFXxO\" width=\"100%\" height=\"232\" frameborder=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allow=\"encrypted-media\"></iframe>"},"excerpt":"<p>Let's get lost in the Asian BerMEDIA Triangle!</p>\n<p>For this season's penultimate episode, we're doing‚Ä¶</p>","html":"<p>Let's get lost in the Asian BerMEDIA Triangle!</p>\n<p>For this season's penultimate episode, we're doing another Asian media review, but in a slightly different style. Join us for 3 mini talks where each of us take on one side of the Asian media triangle (shows/dramas, music/k-pop, and books) to recommend and discuss. Linda also shares <a href=\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00918369.2020.1815428?forwardService=showFullText&#x26;tokenAccess=B2APQPWSVBPWFP7VYJDU&#x26;tokenDomain=eprints&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;target=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;journalCode=wjhm20\">her study on LGBTQ+ Asian American identity and the role of Kpop</a>.</p>\n<p>Sally's recommended dramas/shows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Crash Landing On You</em> </li>\n<li><em>Goblin</em></li>\n<li><em>Hotel del Luna</em></li>\n<li><em>Weightlifting Fairy Kim Bok-joo</em></li>\n<li><em>Reply 1988</em></li>\n<li><em>Giri/Haji</em></li>\n<li><em>The Untamed</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Linda's research article,<a href=\"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00918369.2020.1815428?forwardService=showFullText&#x26;tokenAccess=B2APQPWSVBPWFP7VYJDU&#x26;tokenDomain=eprints&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;doi=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;target=10.1080%2F00918369.2020.1815428&#x26;journalCode=wjhm20\"> <em>Performance, Fantasy, or Narrative: LGBTQ+ Asian American Identity through Kpop Media and Fandom</em></a></p>\n<p>Ming's recommended books:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>If I had your Face</em> by Frances Cha</li>\n<li><em>The Poppy War (trilogy)</em> by R.F. Kuang</li>\n<li><em>Everything I Never Told You</em> by Celeste Ng</li>\n</ul>\n<p>‚Äî‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£</p>\n<p>This episode is in partnership with Teaphile, a queer woman-owned business focusing on single-origin artisan Chinese teas sourced directly from family farms.</p>\n<p>Learn more about their winter subscription program at <a href=\"https://thethirdplace.is/teaphile\">thethirdplace.is/teaphile</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/teaphilelife/?hl=en\">@teaphilelife</a> on Instagram üçÉ</p>","id":"d0424a2a-b45a-5798-8007-d8d823ebdb9a"},"file":{"absolutePath":"/home/sloh/projects/moving-oolong/static/assets/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.jpg","relativePath":"assets/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/0796f62e7b607eaa92e1d755af3b5f10/c0d3d/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.webp","srcSet":"/static/0796f62e7b607eaa92e1d755af3b5f10/73b4e/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.webp 700w,\n/static/0796f62e7b607eaa92e1d755af3b5f10/4506f/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.webp 1401w,\n/static/0796f62e7b607eaa92e1d755af3b5f10/c0d3d/a5fe5f89-dfdf-4296-80df-8af80286d012-971a5e19-4f9c-4eb9-9905-5a4cff258f2e.webp 2801w","sizes":"(min-width: 2801px) 2801px, 100vw"},"sources":[]},"width":2801,"height":2801}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/episode